 This was a phase IV, randomized, double-blind, global, multi-centre study.

 The study consisted of a 2 week screening period followed by an 80 week double-blind treatment period.

 Subjects who met all eligibility requirements were randomized in a 1:1 ratio, stratified by country, gender (male and female) and pre-screening HbA1c (9% or>9) either to MET or AVM.

 When the substudy was added, a new randomization was created for the participating centers.

 Those subjects in the bone sub-study were stratified by country, gender (male, premenopausal female, and postmenopausal female), pre-screening HbA1c (i.

